    "TraceCtxManager depends_on TraceState (for resume/reattach logic)",
    "TraceState associated_with Trace (factory from_trace, serializes to/from JSON)",
    "Scope module-level ContextVars hold current Trace and Span (async/thread-safe)"
  ],

  "important_notes": [
    "Span has parent_id linking to parent span — enables nested span trees within a trace",
    "Span.trace_id links to parent Trace; SpanImpl.export() outputs object='trace.span'",
    "Trace.export() outputs object='trace'; both serialized for TracingProcessor backends",
    "TraceState stores tracing_api_key as SHA-256 hash for secure state snapshots",
    "Scope uses Python contextvars for async-safe current trace/span propagation",
    "_SPAN_METADATA_ROUTING_KEYS = ('agent_harness_id',) — selectively forwarded from trace metadata to span export",
    "NO_OP_TRACE singleton used when tracing disabled globally",
    "trace_id format: 'trace_<32_alphanumeric>' (via util.gen_trace_id); span_id via util.gen_span_id()",
    "GeneratorExit is special-cased in span/trace __exit__ — reset_current=False to avoid corrupting context on generator cleanup"
  ]
